    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 2,
    "last_activity_date" : 1340386602,
    "creation_date" : 1340386602,
    "answer_id" : 11161362,
    "question_id" : 11161248,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>2 errors:</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li><p>You are missing the <code>bin</code> folder.\nUsually the correct path is <code>C:\\Program Files\\Java\\jdk_version\\bin</code></p></li>\n<li><p><code>JAVA_HOME</code> is usually used by some script or program, if you are interested on running java tools from <code>cmd</code> you have to add that directory to <code>PATH</code></p></li>\n</ul>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 404757,
      "reputation" : 23117,
      "user_id" : 773263,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 87,
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/e2581b53db32340d7e1b5be6b99c2bb1?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "Philip Kirkbride",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/773263/philip-kirkbride"
    },
    "is_accepted" : true,
    "score" : 13,
    "last_activity_date" : 1340642766,
    "last_edit_date" : 1495540580,
    "creation_date" : 1340642766,
    "answer_id" : 11193584,
    "question_id" : 11161248,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>As many have mentioned I had to add...</p>\n\n<pre><code>C:\\Program Files\\Java\\jdk_version\\bin\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>...to the path variable.</p>\n\n<p>However what was not mentioned and was stopping this from working was that I had to make sure\njava\\bin directory is in the path statement before the windows\\system32 directory, otherwise this will not work.</p>\n\n<p>I was able to find the information <a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/a/5734845/773263\">here</a>.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 6177253,
      "reputation" : 3243,
      "user_id" : 4813777,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/oAMFb.png?s=256",
      "display_name" : "Taras Melnyk",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/4813777/taras-melnyk"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 12,
    "last_activity_date" : 1539175284,
    "last_edit_date" : 1539175284,
    "creation_date" : 1539174906,
    "answer_id" : 52740410,
    "question_id" : 11161248,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<ol>\n<li><p>Set the <strong>JAVA_HOME</strong> Variable</p>\n\n<p><strong>Windows 7</strong> – Right click My Computer and select Properties > Advanced</p>\n\n<p><strong>Windows 8</strong> – Go to Control Panel > System > Advanced System Settings</p>\n\n<p><strong>Windows 10</strong> – Search for Environment Variables then select Edit the system environment variables</p></li>\n</ol>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/WAorQ.png\" rel=\"noreferrer\"><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/WAorQ.png\" alt=\"enter image description here\"></a></p>\n\n<ol start=\"2\">\n<li><p>Click the <strong>Environment Variables</strong> button.</p></li>\n<li><p>Under <strong>System Variables</strong>, click <strong>New</strong>.</p></li>\n<li><p>In the <strong>Variable Name</strong> field, enter either:</p>\n\n<p><strong>JAVA_HOME</strong> if you installed the JDK (Java Development Kit)</p>\n\n<p>or</p>\n\n<p><strong>JRE_HOME</strong> if you installed the JRE (Java Runtime Environment). In the <strong>Variable Value</strong> field, enter your JDK or JRE installation path .</p></li>\n</ol>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/KOB4s.png\" rel=\"noreferrer\"><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/KOB4s.png\" alt=\"enter image description here\"></a></p>\n\n<ol start=\"5\">\n<li><p>Open Command Prompt as <strong>Administrator</strong>.</p></li>\n<li><p>Set the value of the <strong>Environment variable</strong> to your JDK (or JRE) installation path as follows:</p>\n\n<blockquote>\n  <p>setx -m JAVA_HOME \"C:\\path_to_Java\\jdk_version\"</p>\n</blockquote></li>\n</ol>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 2093262,
      "reputation" : 12058,
      "user_id" : 1862590,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/EX6Kb.png?s=256",
      "display_name" : "Sathiamoorthy",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1862590/sathiamoorthy"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 37,
    "last_activity_date" : 1610343220,
    "creation_date" : 1610343220,
    "answer_id" : 65661794,
    "question_id" : 11161248,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>If you <strong>don't have admin rights</strong>, use the below command to set environment variables for java using the <strong>command prompt</strong></p>\n<pre><code>setx JAVA_HOME &quot;C:\\Program Files\\Java\\jdk1.8.0&quot;\nsetx PATH &quot;%PATH%;%JAVA_HOME%\\bin&quot;;\n</code></pre>\n<p><strong>Modify</strong> the environment variable.</p>\n<pre><code>setx -m JAVA_HOME &quot;C:\\Program Files\\Java\\jdk1.8.0&quot;\nsetx -m PATH &quot;%PATH%;%JAVA_HOME%\\bin&quot;;\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
